<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF81EF42FF12F8CFFCACF864" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF81EF42FF12F8CFFCACF864" blockId="41.[151,1437,1914,2012]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
The 66 species and eight genera of the tribe are distributed in the Neotropical Region, Neartic Region and Mexican Transition Zone. Thirteen species of four genera are recorded for 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF81EF42FCF6F82BFC0EF800" box="[883,955,1950,1976]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Here we report the occurrence of two species of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF81EF42FF6DF877FEC9F864" authority="Fianco &amp; Szinwelski &amp; Faria, 2022" authorityName="Fianco &amp; Szinwelski &amp; Faria" authorityYear="2022" box="[232,380,1986,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="trib. n." tribe="Pycnopalpini">Pycnopalpini</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF81EF42FE4CF877FDE1F864" box="[457,596,1986,2012]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
